Desired Statistics:¶

  • Total Points Won-the total points won by each player divided by the total number of points played. Expressed as a fraction and percentage.

  • Winners-a total count for each player of actions that end in w. Ideally broken down by each stroke type. ex forehand winners, backhand winners, etc. as well as the overall total.

  • Unforced Errors-a total count for each player of actions that end in ue done the same as winners above.

  • Forced Errors-the same as the above winners and unforced errors but for actions that end in fe.

  • Average rally length-the total number of actions by each player once a point has started with a serve in play. Ex. if a player hits a first serve and second serve then only the second serve that went in counts as the rally shot. Typically actions that are errors are also not counted but for now I'd like to try it with all shots that occur after a serve has gone in. I'd like this presented with just the average number (ex. 5.2).

  • I would like the above in total numbers for the whole match as well as for each set played.

points_percentage = {}
for df_set, set_num in [(df_1, 'Set 1'),(df_2, 'Set 2'),(df_3, 'Set 3')]:
    points = df_set.groupby(['game', 'point_number'])['point_winner'].unique()
    total_points = len(points.values)
    total_won_points = [x[0] for x in points.values]
    Michaels_won_points = total_won_points.count('Michaels')
    Harrison_won_points = total_won_points.count('Harrison')
    Michaels_win_fraction = Michaels_won_points / total_points
    Harrison_win_fraction = Harrison_won_points / total_points
    Michaels_fraction = str(Michaels_won_points)+'/'+str(total_points)
    Harrison_fraction = str(Harrison_won_points)+'/'+str(total_points)
    points_percentage[set_num] = [Michaels_fraction, Michaels_win_fraction*100, Harrison_fraction, Harrison_win_fraction*100]

df_points_won_per_set = pd.DataFrame(points_percentage, 
                                     index=pd.MultiIndex.from_tuples([('Michaels', 'Fraction'), ('Michaels', 'Percentage'), ('Harrison', 'Fraction'), ('Harrison', 'Percentage')], 
                                     names=['Player','Form']))
Average = df_points_won_per_set[df_points_won_per_set.index.get_level_values('Form').isin(['Percentage'])].mean(axis=1)
df_points_won_per_set = df_points_won_per_set.merge(Average.rename('Average'), how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True)

Winners¶

A total count for each player of actions that end in w. Ideally broken down by each stroke type. ex forehand winners, backhand winners, etc. as well as the overall total.

Total Winners¶

In [ ]:
def total_shots(shot):
    """
    Count the number of shots that ended the point made by each player in the whole match

    Args:
        shot (str): type of point ender ('fe', 'ue', 'w', etc.)

    Returns:
        Pandas Dataframe of number of shots that ended the point made by each player in the match
    """
    shots = df[df.action.str.contains(shot)].groupby('player_with_action')['action'].value_counts()
    Michaels_shots = pd.DataFrame(shots['Michaels']).rename(columns={'action':'Michaels'})
    Harrison_shots = pd.DataFrame(shots['Harrison']).rename(columns={'action':'Harrison'})
    df_shots = pd.merge(Michaels_shots, Harrison_shots, how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True).fillna(0).astype('int64')
    df_shots.loc['Total Forehand'] = [df_shots[df_shots.index.get_level_values('action').str.startswith('f')]['Michaels'].sum(), df_shots[df_shots.index.get_level_values('action').str.startswith('f')]['Harrison'].sum()]
    df_shots.loc['Total Backhand'] = [df_shots[df_shots.index.get_level_values('action').str.startswith('b')]['Michaels'].sum(), df_shots[df_shots.index.get_level_values('action').str.startswith('b')]['Harrison'].sum()]
    df_shots = df_shots.append(df_shots[:-2].sum().rename('Total'))
    return df_shots

def shots_per_set(shot):  # sourcery skip: list-comprehension
    """
    Count the number of shots that ended the point made by each player in each set and in the whole match

    Args:
        shot (str): type of point ender ('fe', 'ue', 'w', etc.)

    Returns:
        Pandas Dataframe of number of shots that ended the point made by each player in each set and the match
    """
    shots_per_set = df[df.action.str.contains(shot)].groupby(['set', 'player_with_action'])['action'].value_counts()
    df_shots_per_set = pd.DataFrame({'set 1':shots_per_set[1], 'set 2':shots_per_set[2], 'set 3':shots_per_set[3]}).fillna(0).astype('int64')
    players = []
    for player in ['Michaels','Harrison']:
        players.append(df_shots_per_set.loc[player].append([pd.Series(df_shots_per_set.loc[player][df_shots_per_set.loc[player].index.get_level_values('action').str.startswith('f')].sum().values, index=df_shots_per_set.columns, name='Total Forehand'),
                                                            pd.Series(df_shots_per_set.loc[player][df_shots_per_set.loc[player].index.get_level_values('action').str.startswith('b')].sum().values, index=df_shots_per_set.columns, name='Total Backhand'),
                                                            pd.Series(df_shots_per_set.loc[player].sum(), name='All Shots')]))
    df_shots_per_set = pd.concat(players, keys=['Michaels','Harrison'], names=['Player','action'])
    df_shots_per_set = df_shots_per_set.merge(df_shots_per_set.sum(axis=1).rename('Total'), how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True)
    return df_shots_per_set

def plot_shots(df, shot):
    '''Plot a stacked bar chart of dataframe of shots'''
    for a in df.index.get_level_values('action'):
        total_per_player = df[a == df.index.get_level_values('action')]
        if total_per_player.shape[0] == 1:
            for player in ['Michaels','Harrison']:
                if a not in df.loc[player].index.get_level_values('action'):
                    df = df.append(pd.Series(np.full(4,0,'int64'), name=(player, a), index=df.columns))
    shot_sum = []
    for a in df.index.get_level_values('action'):
        total_per_player = df[a == df.index.get_level_values('action')]
        shot_sum.append(total_per_player['Total'].sum())
    
    df = df.merge(pd.Series(shot_sum, name='Total for both palyers', index=df.index), how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True) 
    code = [list(df.index.get_level_values('action').unique()).index(a) for a in df.index.get_level_values('action')]
    df = df.merge(pd.Series(code, index=df.index, name='Code'), how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True)
    harrison_winners = df.loc['Harrison'].sort_values(by=['Total for both palyers','Code'], axis=0)
    michaels_winners = df.loc['Michaels'].sort_values(by=['Total for both palyers','Code'], axis=0)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(25,10))
    p4 = plt.bar(np.arange(len(michaels_winners['set 1']))-0.2, michaels_winners['set 1'], 0.2, align='edge', tick_label=michaels_winners.index, label='Set 1')
    p5 = plt.bar(np.arange(len(michaels_winners['set 2']))-0.2, michaels_winners['set 2'], 0.2, p4.datavalues, align='edge', tick_label=michaels_winners.index, label='Set 2')
    p6 = plt.bar(np.arange(len(michaels_winners['set 3']))-0.2, michaels_winners['set 3'], 0.2, p5.datavalues+p4.datavalues,align='edge', tick_label=michaels_winners.index, label='Set 3')
    
    p4_labels = pd.Series(p4.datavalues).replace(0,'')
    p5_labels = pd.Series(p5.datavalues).replace(0,'')
    p6_labels = pd.Series(p6.datavalues).replace(0,'')
    
    plt.bar_label(p4, p4_labels, label_type='center')
    plt.bar_label(p5, p5_labels, label_type='center')
    plt.bar_label(p6, p6_labels, label_type='center')
    plt.bar_label(p6)
    
    p1 = plt.bar(np.arange(len(harrison_winners['set 1'])), harrison_winners['set 1'], 0.2, align='edge', tick_label=harrison_winners.index, color=p4.patches[0].get_facecolor())
    p2 = plt.bar(np.arange(len(harrison_winners['set 2'])), harrison_winners['set 2'], 0.2, p1.datavalues, align='edge', tick_label=harrison_winners.index, color=p5.patches[0].get_facecolor())
    p3 = plt.bar(np.arange(len(harrison_winners['set 3'])), harrison_winners['set 3'], 0.2, p2.datavalues+p1.datavalues, align='edge', tick_label=harrison_winners.index, color=p6.patches[0].get_facecolor())
    
    p1_labels = pd.Series(p1.datavalues).replace(0,'')
    p2_labels = pd.Series(p2.datavalues).replace(0,'')
    p3_labels = pd.Series(p3.datavalues).replace(0,'')
    
    plt.bar_label(p1, p1_labels, label_type='center')
    plt.bar_label(p2, p2_labels, label_type='center')
    plt.bar_label(p3, p3_labels, label_type='center')
    plt.bar_label(p3)
    
    plt.ylabel('Number of '+shot)
    plt.title("Number of "+shot+" per set for each shot".title())
    plt.legend();

A count of baseline forehands by each player¶

Count of shots that contain f excluding net shots (shots with a v or o). listed as total forehands/forehands + backhands as well as %.

In [ ]:
def baseline_shots_per_set(shot):
    """
    Count the number of shots that ended the point made by each player in each set and in the whole match

    Args:
        shot (str): type of point ender ('fe', 'ue', 'w', etc.)

    Returns:
        Pandas Dataframe of number of shots that ended the point made by each player in each set and the match
    """
    shots_per_set = df[df.action.str.startswith(shot)].groupby(['set', 'player_with_action'])['action'].value_counts()
    df_shots_per_set = pd.DataFrame({'set 1':shots_per_set[1], 'set 2':shots_per_set[2], 'set 3':shots_per_set[3]}).fillna(0).astype('int64')
    df_shots_per_set = df_shots_per_set[np.logical_not((df_shots_per_set.index.get_level_values('action').str.contains('v'))+(df_shots_per_set.index.get_level_values('action').str.contains('o')))]
    players = [
        df_shots_per_set.loc[player].append(
            [pd.Series(df_shots_per_set.loc[player].sum(), name='All Shots')]
        )
        for player in ['Michaels', 'Harrison']
    ]

    df_shots_per_set = pd.concat(players, keys=['Michaels','Harrison'], names=['Player','action'])
    df_shots_per_set = df_shots_per_set.merge(df_shots_per_set.sum(axis=1).rename('Total'), how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True)
    return df_shots_per_set

Average rally length¶

The total number of actions by each player once a point has started with a serve in play. Ex. if a player hits a first serve and second serve then only the second serve that went in counts as the rally shot. Typically actions that are errors are also not counted but for now I'd like to try it with all shots that occur after a serve has gone in. I'd like this presented with just the average number (ex. 5.2).

Average Rally Length in the match¶

In [ ]:
not_counted_rallyshots = ['FSF','FSN','FSL','SSF','SSN','SSL','FSA','SSA']

Rally length 2-4, 5-7, 8-10, 11+¶

This is a breakdown of the number of points in the match that are played within each category of total shots by the players. For example, 1-3 would include points with an ace all the way through to points with a serve, return, and either a winner or error by the server. 4-6 would be rallies with a serve that went in and at least 3 shots by the players up to 5 shots. I would like these expressed as fractions and percentages. For example, 30/100 rallies were 1-4, 20/100 were 5-8, etc. (30% and 20%).

Rally length in the match¶

In [ ]:

_This would show how successful each player was at each rally length. Found by points won at each rally length / total points at that rally length. For example, Player_1 won 30/40 points (75%) at 1-3. Player2 won 10/40 points (25%), etc.

Serve points won¶

_this is the total points won by each player when they are the serving player. I would like it expressed as the amount of points won/total points they served as well as in percentage form. Ex. Player1 serves 70 points and wins 50 of them. This would be expressed as serve points won: 50/70 (71.4%). Note, FSL and SSL (the "L" stands for let) can be ignored here and in all of the rest of the statistics for the time being since lets are not technically points played since they are replayed. I would like to have total serve points won, first serve points won, and second serve points won.

Total serve points won¶

In [ ]:
def serve_points_won(df):
    """
    Returns a dataframe of the fraction and percentage of points won for each player for each set and for the whol match
    """
    winrate_dict = {}
    total_dict = {'Michaels':{'num':[],'total':[]},'Harrison':{'num':[],'total':[]}}
    for set_num in range(1,4):
        winrate_list = []
        for player in ['Michaels','Harrison']:
            winrate = df.loc[player].loc[set_num].value_counts()
            num = winrate[player]
            total = winrate.sum()
            fraction = str(num)+'/'+str(total)
            percentage = (num / total)*100
            winrate_list.append(fraction)
            winrate_list.append(percentage)
            total_dict[player]['num'].append(num)
            total_dict[player]['total'].append(total)
        winrate_dict['Set '+str(set_num)] = winrate_list

    total_list = []
    for player in ['Michaels','Harrison']:
        total_num = sum(total_dict[player]['num'])
        total_total = sum(total_dict[player]['total'])
        total_fraction = str(total_num)+'/'+str(total_total)
        total_percentage = (total_num/total_total)*100
        total_list.append(total_fraction)
        total_list.append(total_percentage)
    winrate_dict['Total'] = total_list

    return pd.DataFrame(winrate_dict, index=pd.MultiIndex.from_tuples([('Michaels', 'Fraction'),
                                                                       ('Michaels', 'Percentage'),
                                                                       ('Harrison', 'Fraction'),
                                                                       ('Harrison', 'Percentage')]))

Aces¶

These are the serve actions FSA (first serve ace) and SSA (second serve ace). I would like the actual number here for total aces, first serve aces, and second serve aces. It would also be great to have aces per first serve. This would just be the percentage of aces out of all first serves (lets in the form of FSL can again be ignored as serves here).

Unreturned serves¶

Serves that went in but were not returned in play by the returning player. Either the serving player hit an ace or the returning player hit the ball out. For this the action of the serving player needs to be FS, FSA, SS or SSA and the first action by the returning player needs to be a shot with an r (returnable serve that was missed), ur (unreturnable serve), ue (unforced error). Expressed as a fraction and percentage ex. 35/70 (50%). I would like to have a total number for this that combines first and second serves as well as for just first serves and just second serves.

Winners/shot¶

Winners (shots containing w)/total shots hit (excluding returns but including net winners (vw or ow for winners and v or o for net containing shots))

In [ ]:
def shot_frequency(df_shot, shots):
    """Returns a dataframe of the fraction and percentage of the shot from the total number of shots hit"""
    global df
    df_total_shots = df.query('action not in @not_counted_rallyshots').groupby(['player_with_action','set','game','point_number'])['action'].apply(np.array)
    if shots == 'All Shots':
        df_total_shots = df_total_shots.apply(lambda x: len(x)-1)
    else:
        shot = 'f' if shots=='Total Forehand' else 'b'
        df_total_shots = df_total_shots.apply(lambda x: len([a for a in x[1:] if a.startswith(shot)]))

    shots_percent_dict = {}
    total_dict = {'Michaels':{'num':[],'total':[]},'Harrison':{'num':[],'total':[]}}
    for set_num in range(1,4):
        shots_percent_list = []
        for player in ['Michaels', 'Harrison']:
            total = df_total_shots[player][set_num].sum()
            num = df_shot['set '+str(set_num)].loc[player, shots]
            shots_fraction = str(num)+'/'+str(total)
            shots_percentage= (num / total)*100
            shots_percent_list.append(shots_fraction)
            shots_percent_list.append(shots_percentage)
            total_dict[player]['num'].append(num)
            total_dict[player]['total'].append(total)
        shots_percent_dict['Set '+str(set_num)] = shots_percent_list

    total_list = []
    for player in ['Michaels','Harrison']:
        total_num = sum(total_dict[player]['num'])
        total_total = sum(total_dict[player]['total'])
        total_fraction = str(total_num)+'/'+str(total_total)
        total_percentage = (total_num/total_total)*100
        total_list.append(total_fraction)
        total_list.append(total_percentage)
    shots_percent_dict['Total'] = total_list

    return pd.DataFrame(
        shots_percent_dict,
        index=pd.MultiIndex.from_tuples(
            [
                ('Michaels', 'Fraction'),
                ('Michaels', 'Percentage'),
                ('Harrison', 'Fraction'),
                ('Harrison', 'Percentage'),
            ]
        ),
    )

Break Points Saved¶

break points are points where the returning player is one point away from winning the game (0-40, 15-40, 30-40, D-A or in the tiebreak anything where the returner has 6 or more points and at least one more point than the server ex. 3-6 would be a break point as would 7-8). This stat would look at all of these break points and take down the amount of points that qualify as break points won / total break point opportunities.

In [ ]:
df_points_scores = pd.DataFrame(df.groupby(['serving','set','game','point_number'])['player1_game_score'].unique())
df_points_scores = df_points_scores.merge(pd.DataFrame(df.groupby(['serving','set','game','point_number'])['player2_game_score'].unique()), how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True)
df_points_scores = df_points_scores.merge(pd.DataFrame(df.groupby(['serving','set','game','point_number'])['point_winner'].unique().rename('player3_game_score')), how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True)

for i in range(1,4):    
    df_points_scores['player'+str(i)+'_game_score'] = df_points_scores['player'+str(i)+'_game_score'].apply(lambda x: x[0])
df_points_scores.columns = ['Michaels_score','Harrison_score','point_winner']

break_point_list = []
for serving, receiving in [('Harrison','Michaels'),('Michaels','Harrison')]:
    serving_df = df_points_scores.loc[serving]
    break_point_list_serving = [
        s in ['40', 'A'] for s in serving_df[receiving + '_score']
    ]
    break_point_list += break_point_list_serving

df_points_scores = df_points_scores.merge(pd.DataFrame(break_point_list, columns=['break_point'], index=df_points_scores.index), how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True)
In [ ]:
df_break_point = df_points_scores.query('break_point')
break_point_dict = {}
total_dict = {'Michaels':{'num':[],'total':[]},'Harrison':{'num':[],'total':[]}}
for set_num in range(1,4):
    break_point_list = []
    for serving, receiving in [('Harrison','Michaels'),('Michaels','Harrison')]:
        try:
            num = df_break_point.loc[serving, set_num]['point_winner'].value_counts()[receiving]
        except KeyError:
            num = 0
        try:
            total = len(df_break_point.loc[serving, set_num])
            break_point_fraction = str(num)+'/'+str(total)
            break_point_percentage = (num / total)*100
        except KeyError:
            break_point_fraction = '0/0'
            break_point_percentage = 0
        break_point_list.append(break_point_fraction)
        break_point_list.append(break_point_percentage)
        total_dict[serving]['num'].append(num)
        total_dict[serving]['total'].append(total)
    break_point_dict['Set '+str(set_num)] = break_point_list

total_list = []
for serving in ['Michaels','Harrison']:
    total_num = sum(total_dict[serving]['num'])
    total_total = sum(total_dict[serving]['total'])
    total_fraction = str(total_num)+'/'+str(total_total)
    total_percentage = (total_num/total_total)*100
    total_list.append(total_fraction)
    total_list.append(total_percentage)
break_point_dict['Total'] = total_list

df_break_point = pd.DataFrame(break_point_dict, index=pd.MultiIndex.from_tuples([('Michaels','Fraction'),
                                                                           ('Michaels','Percentage'),
                                                                           ('Harrison','Fraction'),
                                                                           ('Harrison','Percentage')]))

Games facing break point¶

how many different games the server faced a break point. Ex. the server faced a break point when serving at 0-1, then again in their next service game at 1-2, and finally another one in the second set at 5-4 for three different games with break points. This stat won't count the amount of break points within each game but just how many unique games there was a break point faced.

In [ ]:
df_break_games = df_points_scores.groupby(['serving','set','game']).any().query('break_point').reset_index('game')
break_games_dict = {}
for set_num in range(1,4):
    break_games_num = []
    for serving in ['Michaels','Harrison']:
        try:
            break_games_num.append(len(df_break_games.loc[serving, set_num]))
        except KeyError:
            break_games_num.append(0)
    break_games_dict['Set '+str(set_num)] = break_games_num
df_break_games = pd.DataFrame(break_games_dict, index=['Michaels','Harrison'])
df_break_games = df_break_games.merge(df_break_games.sum(axis=1).rename('Total'), how='outer', left_index=True, right_index=True)

Serve points won when return in play (total, vs 1st serve, vs 2nd serve):¶

This stat filters for serves that went in and the first returning shot by the opponent that also went in. For this aces and faults will be filtered out for the server since it needs to be possible for the returner to get the ball back in play. So for this only FS and SS will be used for the server. For the returner only their first shot after a serve and only shots that went in will be used. First return shots with a ur, r, and ue will not be used.
